<h1>Reviewer2 Conference Management System</h1>

<p>
    Reviewer2 is a web-based platform for organizing and managing academic
    conferences, workshops, and symposia. It supports the complete lifecycle
    of a peer-reviewed academic event.
</p>

<h2>System Overview</h2>

<p>
    The system is designed to assist program chairs, reviewers, and authors
    in coordinating submissions, peer review, and decision-making in a 
    structured and transparent manner.
</p>

<h2>What you can do</h2>

<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Create and configure conferences</strong><br />
        Define important dates, submission tracks, and review policies.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Manage paper submissions</strong><br />
        Collect manuscripts, revisions, and supplementary material.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Coordinate the peer-review process</strong><br />
        Assign reviewers, monitor reviews, and make acceptance decisions.
    </li>
</ul>

<h2>Typical Conference Workflow</h2>

<ol>
    <li>Conference creation and configuration</li>
    <li>Paper submission by authors</li>
    <li>Reviewer bidding and assignment</li>
    <li>Peer review and discussion</li>
    <li>Acceptance and rejection decisions</li>
    <li>Camera-ready paper submission</li>
</ol>

<h2>Getting Started</h2>

<p>
    Use the navigation menu to get registered, or sign-in to access your conference portal.
</p>

